like my dad.

15:03.408 --> 15:05.558
I would lead
a normal life.

15:05.610 --> 15:08.912
I just wouldn't...Be able
to play basketball.

15:08.996 --> 15:11.782
Which is completely
unacceptable.

15:11.866 --> 15:14.000
Nate,
we worked so hard!

15:14.068 --> 15:16.353
Come on, man. Shut up.
I want to hear this.

15:16.421 --> 15:18.789
Are they sure
that you couldn't play?

15:18.873 --> 15:20.674
There are a couple
of unique cases

15:20.742 --> 15:23.176
where guys going through this
have played,

15:23.244 --> 15:25.078
but I --
I wouldn't be one of them.

15:25.129 --> 15:27.464
Maybe they could
find a donor.

15:27.548 --> 15:29.249
Ah, that's right.
That is right.

15:29.300 --> 15:30.350
Good point, hales.

15:30.417 --> 15:31.718
He's getting worse,
hales.

15:33.855 --> 15:35.238
What if
that were me in there?

15:35.306 --> 15:36.556
What would you say
to Clay?

15:36.624 --> 15:38.091
That's not fair.
That's not fair.

15:38.142 --> 15:40.310
Clay could still
do what he loves.

15:40.361 --> 15:41.978
He could still be an Agent.

15:43.781 --> 15:47.334
I don't know, baby.
You've worked so hard.

15:47.401 --> 15:49.402
That's what I said.

15:51.272 --> 15:54.241
They ran some tests
on my back.

15:54.292 --> 15:55.659
It's getting worse.

15:55.743 --> 15:57.711
What?

15:57.778 --> 16:01.081
I didn't tell you because
of Clay and Quinn and Brooke

16:01.132 --> 16:04.918
and everything that
you've had to deal with, but...

16:05.002 --> 16:06.753
My back
is degenerating.

16:06.804 --> 16:10.173
♪ Even if you're strong ♪

16:10.258 --> 16:12.259
I could
maybe play this season

16:12.310 --> 16:14.511
or even next
and it could be fine,

16:14.595 --> 16:16.897
but nobody
can really say for sure.

16:16.964 --> 16:19.015
The only thing
we do know for sure

16:19.100 --> 16:22.602
is that if I do this
for Clay...

16:22.653 --> 16:24.604
I could save his life.

16:24.655 --> 16:27.407
♪ Forever ♪

16:27.474 --> 16:30.410
I love you.

16:30.477 --> 16:33.613
I love the person that you are,
your strength.

16:33.664 --> 16:35.248
♪ This song is forever ♪

16:35.316 --> 16:37.217
where do you think
I learned it?

16:37.285 --> 16:43.406
♪ I-I-I'll, I'll be ♪

16:43.474 --> 16:48.161
♪ I-I-I'll, I'll be ♪

16:48.212 --> 16:50.046
I can't believe
he's giving up the game.

16:50.131 --> 16:51.998
Oh, come on, man.
He's doing this for you.

16:52.049 --> 16:54.334
Besides, you heard him.
His back is all screwed up.

16:54.385 --> 16:57.003
We don't know that for sure.
He's using me as an excuse.

16:57.054 --> 16:58.671
He's saving your life.

16:58.723 --> 17:00.690
You know what?
Why don't you just
stay out of this!

17:00.775 --> 17:02.108
I don't even know you.

17:02.176 --> 17:04.227
I think you might
want to remember

17:04.311 --> 17:05.896
what you could lose,
Clay.

17:13.069 --> 17:14.854
How 'bout you just
say "thank you"?

17:29.220 --> 17:31.588
There's a moment
in "field of dreams"

17:31.672 --> 17:35.759
where moonlight Graham knows
he'll never play the game again.

17:35.843 --> 17:38.094
And he's at ease with it

17:38.179 --> 17:41.681
because he had his moment
in the sun.

17:41.732 --> 17:45.268
And because he had
something else in his life

17:45.386 --> 17:47.571
to take the game's place.

17:47.655 --> 17:50.273
You have a good day,
Buddy?
Yeah.

17:50.358 --> 17:51.942
How are Clay
and aunt Quinn?

17:52.026 --> 17:55.195
Uh, aunt Quinn's
doing better.

17:55.246 --> 17:58.798
But, uh,
Clay's not doing so good.

17:58.866 --> 18:01.284
He needs
a kidney transplant, Jamie,

18:01.369 --> 18:03.336
so they're gonna see
if they can take one from me.

18:03.404 --> 18:05.205
Will you be okay?
Yeah. I'll be fine.

18:05.273 --> 18:07.740
Um...

18:07.792 --> 18:10.377
I won't be able to play
basketball anymore, though.

18:10.478 --> 18:11.678
Do you have to?

18:11.745 --> 18:13.513
Give Clay your kidney?

18:13.580 --> 18:15.265
No.

18:15.349 --> 18:16.633
No, I don't have to.

18:16.750 --> 18:19.352
But if I don't,
then Clay might not get one.

18:19.420 --> 18:22.022
And if Clay
doesn't get one...

18:22.089 --> 18:24.190
He might never wake up.

18:24.258 --> 18:25.925
Maybe he could
have <i>my</i> kidney.

18:25.977 --> 18:29.145
That way he would be okay and
you could still be a bobcat.

18:29.213 --> 18:31.731
I think you're a little young
for that, jame.

18:31.782 --> 18:33.733
I love you
for the offer, though,

18:33.784 --> 18:35.418
and I know
Clay would, too.

18:35.486 --> 18:38.722
Do you understand how important
this is for Clay, Buddy?

18:38.789 --> 18:39.939
Okay.

18:39.991 --> 18:42.292
I know you loved
that I was a bobcat,

18:42.376 --> 18:45.128
so I understand
if you're a little disappointed.

18:45.212 --> 18:47.914
But just...

18:47.965 --> 18:49.716
Just try
to think about Clay, okay?

18:51.719 --> 18:54.220
We'll talk about this more
in the morning.

18:54.288 --> 18:55.455
I love you, Buddy.

18:55.506 --> 18:58.892
I love you, too.

18:58.959 --> 19:00.927
Hey, dad?

19:00.995 --> 19:03.647
Clay's the reason you were
gonna be a bobcat this year,

19:03.714 --> 19:05.815
so if he needs help,
we should help him.

19:05.900 --> 19:08.718
You're a good man,
Jamie Scott.

19:08.786 --> 19:10.937
So are you, dad.

19:10.988 --> 19:16.526
♪ All the way ♪

19:16.610 --> 19:23.033
♪ and I'll be there
to guide you all the way ♪

19:23.117 --> 19:24.000
Quinny.

19:24.085 --> 19:26.252
♪ There's nowhere left to hide ♪

19:26.320 --> 19:27.587
Quinn!

19:27.672 --> 19:30.656
♪ I'll come through
and turn the tide ♪

19:30.708 --> 19:33.343
promise me
you're well enough for this.

19:33.427 --> 19:37.630
♪ All the way ♪

19:43.471 --> 19:48.308
♪ for love ♪

19:52.213 --> 19:57.901
♪ for love ♪

19:57.985 --> 20:05.992
♪ ooooh oooh, for love ♪

20:06.043 --> 20:07.860
are you okay?

20:07.912 --> 20:10.630
Yeah.

20:10.697 --> 20:12.632
I'll be outside.

20:12.699 --> 20:14.534
♪ To let your heart... ♪

20:14.585 --> 20:16.803
thanks.

20:20.174 --> 20:28.714
♪ And I'll be
right beside you all the way ♪

20:30.267 --> 20:32.652
hi, honey.

20:32.719 --> 20:34.904
It's me.

20:34.989 --> 20:38.024
♪ There's nowhere left to hide ♪

20:38.075 --> 20:40.076
I'm right here.

20:40.161 --> 20:44.230
♪ I'll come through
and turn the tide ♪

20:44.281 --> 20:46.449
♪ all the way ♪

20:46.534 --> 20:51.571
♪ all the way ♪

20:51.622 --> 20:55.325
♪ for love ♪

21:10.226 --> 21:12.043
Hey, handsome.

21:14.614 --> 21:17.215
You know,
my whole family was here.

21:17.283 --> 21:20.352
It's usually best
to be in a coma for that,

21:20.403 --> 21:22.737
so...Nice work.

21:25.441 --> 21:26.741
I also need to tell you

21:26.826 --> 21:28.443
that it's gonna take longer

21:28.528 --> 21:30.662
to get into Nathan's basketball
games next year

21:30.729 --> 21:33.865
because my right boob is gonna
set off the metal detector.

21:36.202 --> 21:38.537
Apparently, I still
have the bullet in me,

21:38.588 --> 21:41.406
so you can cross that off
your fantasy-girl wish list.

21:46.929 --> 21:49.131
So just between us,

21:49.215 --> 21:53.702
everybody's putting on
a really brave face,

21:53.769 --> 21:57.222
but I think
they're all really scared.

21:57.273 --> 22:00.592
Because they can't imagine
losing you.

22:00.643 --> 22:04.429
It's too much to imagine.

22:04.480 --> 22:09.767
But that's not gonna happen,
is it?

22:09.819 --> 22:12.621
My man is too strong for that.

22:15.041 --> 22:18.827
So why don't --
why don't you surprise us all...

22:18.911 --> 22:22.547
And open
those beautiful blue eyes

22:22.615 --> 22:24.266
and take my breath away

22:24.333 --> 22:26.485
like you know you do.

22:26.552 --> 22:28.420
Just open those eyes...

22:30.789 --> 22:33.425
...That see me
like no eyes ever have.

22:36.128 --> 22:38.730
And I'll be right here waiting.

22:55.147 --> 22:57.682
♪ get yourself a limbo girl ♪

22:57.750 --> 23:00.268
♪ give that chick
a limbo whirl ♪

23:00.336 --> 23:03.205
♪ there's a limbo moon
above ♪

23:03.272 --> 23:05.340
♪ you will fall
in limbo love ♪

23:08.827 --> 23:11.463
I took the moon
for granted.

23:11.514 --> 23:14.933
I wouldn't do that
anymore, if I lived.

23:15.000 --> 23:18.653
I also like to think
I'd be nicer to people, too.

23:18.721 --> 23:22.941
'M not saying I <i>would</i> be,
but I'd like to think I would.

23:25.978 --> 23:28.530
You're supposed to talk now.

23:30.983 --> 23:33.201
The girl who shot me
shot Quinn, too.

23:33.286 --> 23:36.154
The thing is...

23:36.205 --> 23:40.458
She compelled me,
at first.

23:40.526 --> 23:46.364
I mean, she was, uh,
just imbalanced and obsessive.

23:46.415 --> 23:49.701
I've just been thinking,
and, um...

23:49.752 --> 23:51.386
I don't know, man.

23:51.470 --> 23:54.222
Maybe I, uh,
maybe I led her on.

23:54.307 --> 23:55.707
No.

23:55.758 --> 23:59.144
No. Crazy is crazy.

23:59.211 --> 24:00.929
It's not your fault.

24:01.013 --> 24:04.516
♪ Every limbo
boy and girl ♪

24:04.567 --> 24:08.052
♪ all around
the limbo world ♪

24:09.272 --> 24:10.655
What? It's catchy.

24:14.110 --> 24:15.827
Hey, can I
ask you something?

24:18.781 --> 24:21.866
You know
what comes next?

24:21.917 --> 24:23.918
You know,
like if we die?

24:24.003 --> 24:26.755
I've been kind of worried
about that.

24:26.839 --> 24:30.542
No. I don't know
what comes next.

24:30.593 --> 24:33.178
And I don't want to know.

24:33.245 --> 24:34.212
Yeah.

24:36.182 --> 24:38.516
Like I said...

24:38.584 --> 24:41.386
I've been worried
about it.

24:45.708 --> 24:48.460
♪ Jack be limbo,
Jack be quick ♪

24:51.564 --> 24:54.165
I took Quinn
to see Clay tonight.

24:56.869 --> 24:59.437
She tried to be brave,
but you could --

24:59.488 --> 25:02.090
you could see the desperation
in her eyes.

25:04.777 --> 25:07.312
I remember
sitting in the hospital

25:07.380 --> 25:09.947
after
the state championship game.

25:09.999 --> 25:12.434
I was praying
that you'd wake up,

25:12.501 --> 25:15.053
just sitting there,

25:15.121 --> 25:17.355
desperate, helpless...

25:19.392 --> 25:22.060
And responsible.

25:24.096 --> 25:26.648
But here we are.

25:26.732 --> 25:30.134
You were pregnant with Jamie
that night.

25:30.186 --> 25:31.603
Mm-hmm.

25:31.654 --> 25:35.323
I remember thinking that I
didn't want to lose what we had.

25:35.408 --> 25:38.460
But I also didn't want to lose
what we'd <i>have...</i>

25:38.527 --> 25:41.830
The rest of our lives
together...

25:44.166 --> 25:46.101
...Our family...

25:46.168 --> 25:49.371
Our someday.

25:49.455 --> 25:53.007
That's all she wants --
someday.

25:54.710 --> 25:56.678
They deserve that.

25:59.482 --> 26:02.467
Everyone deserves that.

26:03.369 --> 26:06.939
It was nice
having Jamie today.

26:06.992 --> 26:10.278
I don't know
if I'm allowed to say it,

26:10.362 --> 26:13.898
but despite everything,
it was a good day.

26:13.949 --> 26:16.618
He likes
being with his aunt Brooke.

26:16.702 --> 26:18.786
No, he likes
being with <i>you,</i>

26:18.871 --> 26:21.456
and I like
seeing you two together.

26:21.540 --> 26:23.791
I love that
you're so good to him.

26:23.859 --> 26:26.243
Does it make you
a little sad?

26:28.597 --> 26:30.348
Yeah.

26:30.415 --> 26:32.350
I know.

26:34.403 --> 26:37.055
So what's happening
with the company?

26:37.106 --> 26:40.024
My mom says
that we're keeping the company,

26:40.092 --> 26:43.444
and that she and the attorneys
can handle everything.

26:43.529 --> 26:45.196
But do we trust her
this time?

26:45.263 --> 26:46.664
Honestly?

26:49.201 --> 26:51.069
I don't know
if I'll ever trust her again.

26:55.240 --> 26:56.491
Damn it.

26:56.575 --> 27:02.046
♪ ...We live tonight ♪

27:02.114 --> 27:07.135
♪ the day you finally
turn to dust ♪

27:07.219 --> 27:08.336
that's Brooke.

27:08.420 --> 27:10.421
Don't you think
you should take it?

27:10.472 --> 27:12.306
I'll talk to her
eventually.

27:12.391 --> 27:13.791
But --
where were we?

27:13.842 --> 27:15.810
You know, Victoria,
I know you're trying to help,

27:15.894 --> 27:17.512
but this is
how we got here.

27:17.596 --> 27:19.597
I <i>hate</i> that I didn't involve
Brooke the last time,

27:19.648 --> 27:21.132
and I don't feel good
about it now.

27:21.183 --> 27:22.900
I understand that.

27:22.968 --> 27:24.519
And I respect it.

27:24.603 --> 27:26.104
But consider this --

27:26.155 --> 27:28.773
if we <i>had</i> involved Brooke
the last time,

27:28.824 --> 27:31.275
she'd be going to prison
instead of me.

27:33.445 --> 27:35.246
Is that
what you'd prefer?

27:35.313 --> 27:37.331
No.

27:37.416 --> 27:39.867
Okay.
So where were we?

27:39.952 --> 27:42.170
You were talking about
how to deal with the press.

27:42.254 --> 27:44.255
Yes. You're gonna have to
do some research.

27:44.322 --> 27:47.508
♪ Ooh ooh-ooh ♪

27:47.593 --> 27:50.628
♪ ooh ooh ooooh ♪

27:50.679 --> 27:53.931
♪ we'll ring the bells
that lead you home ♪

27:53.999 --> 27:56.567
"Brian's song"
was a true story --

27:56.635 --> 28:00.521
a Buddy film, a sports tale,
an emotional tearjerker,

28:00.606 --> 28:04.392
all wrapped up into one great
underdog sports movie.

28:04.476 --> 28:08.646
But at its core, "brian's song"
was a tale of two friends --

28:08.697 --> 28:10.181
one who was dying,

28:10.232 --> 28:13.684
and one who would've given
anything to save him.

28:13.736 --> 28:15.453
I'm sorry, Nathan.

28:15.520 --> 28:17.021
You're not a match.

28:17.072 --> 28:22.660
♪ ...We live tonight ♪

28:22.711 --> 28:28.199
♪ at least we live tonight ♪

28:37.517 --> 28:41.436
there has to be something
we can do.

28:41.487 --> 28:43.655
Yeah, um...

28:43.740 --> 28:46.658
Tay says you've been calling
everybody in the family

28:46.743 --> 28:48.110
shopping for a kidney.

28:48.161 --> 28:51.747
There has to be <i>something.</i>

28:53.783 --> 28:56.585
He doesn't have
much time, Quinn.

28:56.652 --> 28:58.470
♪ The Sea ♪

29:03.176 --> 29:05.711
♪ the breeze ♪

29:11.217 --> 29:13.335
I'm sorry.

29:13.386 --> 29:18.673
♪ Red October leaves ♪

29:23.179 --> 29:26.565
♪ Couldn't keep ♪

29:26.649 --> 29:30.852
I don't -- I don't want to live
without you, okay?

29:35.908 --> 29:38.043
Hey.

29:44.700 --> 29:47.135
♪ And it isn't the way... ♪

29:47.203 --> 29:48.253
hey.

29:48.338 --> 29:51.890
♪ ...You hold a gaze ♪

29:51.958 --> 29:57.346
♪ and isn't the way
you take the wave ♪

29:57.397 --> 29:59.231
hey.

29:59.315 --> 30:01.566
♪ The way it feels... ♪

30:06.406 --> 30:07.990
I'm sorry.

30:10.559 --> 30:12.361
I love you so much,

30:12.412 --> 30:16.331
and this world is too big
and it's too dark

30:16.399 --> 30:19.601
and it's too much
if you leave it.

30:26.759 --> 30:28.093
I know this sucks,

30:28.161 --> 30:30.379
but it's got to
be nice to know

30:30.430 --> 30:32.747
that someone loves you
like that.

30:32.799 --> 30:35.217
♪ Love ♪

30:39.005 --> 30:42.024
♪ lost ♪

30:45.478 --> 30:49.764
♪ love ♪

30:52.935 --> 30:56.488
♪ lost ♪

30:59.826 --> 31:02.327
♪ love ♪

31:08.301 --> 31:13.672
♪ lost ♪

31:13.756 --> 31:18.427
♪ love ♪

31:22.849 --> 31:27.686
♪ lost ♪

31:27.770 --> 31:31.073
♪ love ♪

31:35.078 --> 31:40.832
♪ lost ♪

31:40.917 --> 31:43.651
♪ love ♪

31:49.509 --> 31:54.679
♪ lost ♪

31:54.764 --> 31:56.798
♪ love ♪

32:01.671 --> 32:05.690
♪ you see ♪

32:07.777 --> 32:10.345
♪ What it means
to be free ♪

32:15.851 --> 32:24.359
♪ you're a setting sun
for everyone to see ♪

32:32.802 --> 32:36.138
Brooke and Julian
picked up Jamie.

32:36.205 --> 32:39.057
I'm not strong enough
for this.

32:41.260 --> 32:47.215
My whole life, I've willed
myself to face things.

32:47.266 --> 32:49.551
Anything that was bigger
than me,

32:49.602 --> 32:51.436
anything that defeated me,

32:51.521 --> 32:54.022
I just kept going
until I beat it.

32:57.276 --> 33:00.912
Not this.

33:00.997 --> 33:02.697
This is too big.

33:05.868 --> 33:08.420
I never really understood
what you faced

33:08.504 --> 33:10.755
when you lost your mom
until today.

33:13.793 --> 33:16.211
I'm not strong enough,
Haley.

33:17.346 --> 33:19.581
Yes, you are.

33:21.801 --> 33:24.970
And when you're not,
you have me.

33:25.054 --> 33:28.857
What are we gonna do?

33:28.924 --> 33:31.443
"What are we gonna do?"

33:31.527 --> 33:35.614
On the Eve of the fight of his
life, rocky balboa can't sleep.

33:35.698 --> 33:37.765
So he goes to the arena,

33:37.817 --> 33:41.953
and finding no comfort there,
he goes home to Adrian.

33:42.038 --> 33:43.788
She wakes up and sits with him,

33:43.873 --> 33:45.824
there in the shadows
of the night,

33:45.908 --> 33:48.443
and he confesses
that he can't win.

33:48.494 --> 33:50.829
It's a fight he's going to lose.

33:50.913 --> 33:54.799
And Adrian waits for a moment,
and then she says...

33:54.884 --> 33:57.219
What are we gonna do?

33:59.755 --> 34:02.507
"What are we gonna do?"

34:02.592 --> 34:04.759
Not "what are <i>you</i> gonna do,"

34:04.827 --> 34:07.596
but "what are <i>we</i> gonna do?"

34:07.647 --> 34:10.632
And that's what I love
about "rocky."

34:10.683 --> 34:12.851
He knew he wasn't gonna win.

34:12.935 --> 34:14.268
He didn't win.

34:16.405 --> 34:18.356
Good night, aunt Brooke.
Good night, Julian.

34:18.440 --> 34:19.574
Good night, Buddy.

34:19.641 --> 34:20.909
Sleep tight.

34:20.976 --> 34:22.810
Aunt Brooke,
Julian --

34:22.862 --> 34:25.030
you guys are gonna make
great parents someday.

34:27.116 --> 34:30.034
He didn't get
everything he wished for.

34:35.041 --> 34:38.826
But he stayed on his feet
long enough to find love.

34:47.170 --> 34:49.504
Please don't be the police.

34:54.260 --> 34:55.877
Hi.

34:55.928 --> 34:57.713
Millie,
<i>what</i> are you doing here?

34:57.764 --> 34:58.913
It's early.

34:58.965 --> 35:00.966
I know. I need
to tell you something.

35:05.294 --> 35:07.295
Mom?

35:10.178 --> 35:11.945
She told you,
didn't she?

35:11.997 --> 35:16.050
Is it true?
Are you going to prison?

35:16.117 --> 35:18.052
Well, it's --
it's white collar.

35:18.119 --> 35:20.171
It's more of a country club,
really.

35:20.255 --> 35:22.590
It's <i>prison,</i> mother.

35:22.641 --> 35:24.925
How could you do this?

35:24.976 --> 35:27.461
Because you're my daughter,
and I love you.

35:28.963 --> 35:32.400
I don't want you to go.

35:32.467 --> 35:35.686
It's my fault.

35:38.940 --> 35:41.659
We should get confetti.

35:41.743 --> 35:44.528
For when Clay wakes up.

35:44.613 --> 35:48.833
Honey, Uncle Clay
is very sick.

35:48.917 --> 35:50.284
I know.

35:50.335 --> 35:52.653
But remember when you won
the state championship game?

35:52.704 --> 35:54.338
And Uncle Lucas
made the winning shot?

35:54.456 --> 35:56.340
Remember how that felt?

35:56.425 --> 35:58.542
Mm-hmm.

35:58.627 --> 36:02.847
So, I think
it's gonna feel like that

36:02.931 --> 36:04.632
when Clay wakes up.

36:04.683 --> 36:05.766
So we should
get confetti.

36:08.002 --> 36:09.970
I love you.
You know that?

36:10.021 --> 36:13.674
♪ I'm all out of words ♪

36:13.725 --> 36:15.309
I love you.

36:15.360 --> 36:17.394
You know that?

36:17.479 --> 36:20.564
♪ ...To you ♪

36:20.632 --> 36:25.853
but I want to talk to you
about Sara.

36:25.904 --> 36:30.023
Because I know how much
you loved her,

36:30.075 --> 36:32.359
and how much she loved you.

36:35.046 --> 36:38.999
And I don't -- I don't know
how it works in heaven,

36:39.050 --> 36:42.369
but I'm sure that
they have a plan for that.

36:44.038 --> 36:46.490
For you to be with her but...

36:46.558 --> 36:50.344
But to also be with me.

36:50.395 --> 36:53.848
Because in my heaven...

36:53.899 --> 36:55.883
It's just us.

36:57.869 --> 36:59.253
You and me.

37:02.040 --> 37:05.526
They must have
a plan for that.

37:05.577 --> 37:07.912
♪ To come undone ♪

37:10.499 --> 37:13.534
I'm in love with Quinn.

37:13.585 --> 37:17.121
But I had a wife
that I used to love, too,

37:17.205 --> 37:19.190
but she died.

37:19.257 --> 37:20.875
How do you suppose
that works?

37:20.926 --> 37:22.293
I don't know.

37:22.377 --> 37:23.744
It just does.

37:23.795 --> 37:25.029
You think?

37:25.096 --> 37:27.848
Because I've been
trying to make sense of it,

37:27.916 --> 37:28.933
and I can't.

37:29.017 --> 37:30.100
So what?

37:30.185 --> 37:31.936
Look, this doesn't
make sense, does it?

37:32.020 --> 37:34.104
Couple of ghosts
sitting on a roof?

37:34.172 --> 37:36.473
But here we are.

37:36.558 --> 37:38.192
I never asked you,

37:38.259 --> 37:40.561
but, uh,
how'd you get here?

37:40.612 --> 37:42.613
Car accident.

37:42.697 --> 37:44.865
I'm sorry.

37:44.933 --> 37:46.901
Nah, it was my fault.

37:46.968 --> 37:48.502
I was texting.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.404
Dude...

37:50.455 --> 37:52.740
Do you know
how <i>stupid</i> that is?

37:52.791 --> 37:55.176
I do now.

37:56.444 --> 37:58.045
So what's your name,
anyway?

37:59.664 --> 38:01.782
It's will.

38:01.833 --> 38:05.419
Most great stories
are stories of will,

38:05.470 --> 38:09.256
of determination and courage
in the face of great adversity,

38:09.307 --> 38:12.676
of the will to win,
of the will to fight,

38:12.761 --> 38:15.229
of the will to survive.

38:17.515 --> 38:20.434
♪ Let me pray you through ♪

38:23.405 --> 38:26.824
♪ let me pray you through ♪

38:28.326 --> 38:31.979
I love you, Quinn.

38:38.837 --> 38:42.172
I don't know
how to do this.

38:42.240 --> 38:45.993
I guess you'll know
when you know.

38:46.044 --> 38:47.828
I don't want to die.

38:47.879 --> 38:50.798
Most great movies, whether
sports films or otherwise,

38:50.849 --> 38:53.300
remind us of why we're here,

38:53.351 --> 38:57.354
of how precious
and precarious our lives are.

39:00.058 --> 39:02.843
And of how lucky we are
to have each other.

39:06.681 --> 39:08.682
It was good
hanging with you.

39:08.733 --> 39:10.567
Yeah.

39:12.153 --> 39:14.955
It's not your fault.

39:15.023 --> 39:18.926
♪ ...But I always want more ♪

39:18.994 --> 39:21.979
♪ there was something
I was needing ♪

39:22.047 --> 39:27.367
♪ something you were keeping ♪

39:28.787 --> 39:31.305
I love you, Clay Evans.

39:31.372 --> 39:33.007
Till kingdom come.

39:33.058 --> 39:36.727
♪ ...The rest of my days... ♪

